About me

   I am a "Directeur de Recherche" (i.e. tenured research professor) with
   Inria, the French National Institute for Research in Computer Science
   and Control.

   I am also serving as Inria's deputy scientific director for the fields
   "Digital health, biology and earth".

   My research activities are carried out with Inria Project-Team Beagle,
   that is also co-affiliated with the LIRIS laboratory.

   We are located in Lyon, France.

